---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About the architecture and operating philosophy behind DWILL Blog."
>
  <div class="page-center page-center-narrow">
    <section class="page-intro page-intro-center">
      <p>About</p>
      <h1>System Philosophy</h1>
    </section>

    <section class="surface-inline-grid" aria-label="About system goals">
      <article class="surface-card">
        <p class="surface-kicker">Architecture</p>
        <h3>Static-first publishing</h3>
        <p>Markdown content, deterministic build, and host-independent output.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="surface-card">
        <p class="surface-kicker">Migration</p>
        <h3>Cloudflare now, VPS later</h3>
        <p>Identical URL and artifact model for deployment portability.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="surface-card">
        <p class="surface-kicker">Performance</p>
        <h3>Low-runtime strategy</h3>
        <p>Minimal JS on content pages and static route pre-generation.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="surface-card">
        <p class="surface-kicker">Design</p>
        <h3>Distinctive but lean</h3>
        <p>A visual signature with constrained dependencies and maintainable code.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="prose-flow">
      <h2>Design Goals</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Extreme simplicity in codebase structure and operation.</li>
        <li>Fast cold-load performance with minimal runtime JavaScript.</li>
        <li>Long-term maintainability for continuous publishing.</li>
        <li>A distinctive visual language without heavy front-end overhead.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
